ce:section.ce:para:
In this work, citric acid and 3,5-diaminobenzoic acid have been used as precursors to successfully synthesize green fluorescent carbon dots (G-CDs) through one-step hydrothermal method. As-obtained G-CDs show low toxicity and excellent biocompatibility. Benefiting from these exceptional properties, as-synthesized G-CDs have been utilized to target nucleolus built on DNA-sensitive properties of G-CDs. More surprisingly, nucleolus-targeted property enables G-CDs to carry exogenous DNA molecules into nucleolus, which displays considerable application prospects in gene therapy. What’s more, G-CDs can be constructed as a biosensing platform to identify NO2
                     – and pH in living cells (Scheme 1
                     ).
